BEGIN_TEXT
Solve the equation \( \sin(4x)+\sin(x) = 0 \)
for values of \( x \) in the interval
\( 0 < x < 2\pi \) by applying an identity
to the left hand side of the equation.
$PAR
\( x = \) \{ ans_rule(50) \}
\{ AnswerFormatHelp("numbers") \}
END_TEXT
